# SciWeb 3.0 Project Structure

SciWeb 3.0 is a Flask-based web application for educational knowledge mapping and academic collaboration.

## Main Components

- [app.py](mdc:app.py) - Main Flask application entry point with route definitions
- [templates/](mdc:templates/) - HTML templates using Jinja2 templating system
- [static/](mdc:static/) - Static assets (CSS, JavaScript, images)
- [firebase_routes.py](mdc:firebase_routes.py) - API routes for Firebase database operations
- [ai_routes.py](mdc:ai_routes.py) - AI functionality routes

## Key Templates

- [templates/base.html](mdc:templates/base.html) - Base template with common layout elements
- [templates/login.html](mdc:templates/login.html) - Login page
- [templates/signup.html](mdc:templates/signup.html) - User registration page
- [templates/profile.html](mdc:templates/profile.html) - User profile page
- [templates/tree.html](mdc:templates/tree.html) - Knowledge web visualization

## Frontend Assets

- **CSS Files:**
  - [static/css/style.css](mdc:static/css/style.css) - Main application styles
  - [static/css/login.css](mdc:static/css/login.css) - Login page styles
  - [static/css/profile.css](mdc:static/css/profile.css) - Profile page styles

- **JavaScript Files:**
  - [static/js/main.js](mdc:static/js/main.js) - Main application JavaScript
  - [static/js/login.js](mdc:static/js/login.js) - Login page functionality
  - [static/js/auth-nav.js](mdc:static/js/auth-nav.js) - Authentication state in navigation
  - [static/js/profile.js](mdc:static/js/profile.js) - Profile page functionality

## Database

SciWeb 3.0 uses Firebase Firestore as its database:

- [database.md](mdc:database.md) - Database schema documentation
- Main collections:
  - `Members` - User account information
  - `Trees` - User's knowledge web data

## Routes Structure

- `/` - Home page
- `/login` - Login page
- `/signup` - User registration
- `/profile` - User profile management
- `/tree` - Knowledge web interface
- `/schedule` - User schedule view
- `/api/*` - Firebase data operations
- `/ai/*` - AI-powered features
